@NODE "Mail.0" "Yes, it`s the cpu blitting again.....<sigh>"
    2 Jul 98 23:22:57 +0100
    2 Jul 98 23:22:37 +0100
From: "Dermot Smyth" <D.P.Smyth@sheffield.ac.uk>
Subject: Yes, it`s the cpu blitting again.....<sigh>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 1998 23:22:37 +0100
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_0005_01BDA610.5EB43D80"

This is a multi-part message in MIME format.

------=_NextPart_000_0005_01BDA610.5EB43D80
	boundary="----=_NextPart_001_0006_01BDA610.5EB43D80"


------=_NextPart_001_0006_01BDA610.5EB43D80
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi Dave,

Thanks for the example you sent, it worked.  But unfortunately it was in =
amiga mode and my game is in blitz mode so I couldn`t really get much =
from it.
I am still getting the corrupt display when I run my example program.  =
This is weird because FAST BITMAP to CHIP works fine, but for some =
reason SUPERBITMAP-FASTBUFFER-CHIP doesn`t, and I don`t know why.  At =
first I thought it was widths but I made all the bitmaps the same width =
and it still happened. Its nothing to do with the scroll increment =
either because I copied a screen size chunk SUPERBITMAP - CHIP and it =
was still corrupted.  I think there is something I don`t know about, =
that is why I have included the program.
What about these memtype numbers?
Can other people on the list take a look as well? Particularily those =
that are using Dave`s cpu routines, the more eyes the better!
The quicker I can get `em working the quicker I can stop sending these =
pathetic whines to the list!!!!
You all must be very sick of it by now.

>>>>ALEX<<<< Smyth

------=_NextPart_001_0006_01BDA610.5EB43D80
	charset="iso-8859-1"

