@NODE "Mail.23" "Visual Blitz?"
 19 Jul 1998 20:42:23 +0100 (BST)
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 1998 15:34:31 +0000
From: Andrew <mramiga@assign.u-net.com>
Subject: Visual Blitz?

This is a bit out the realms of this maillist but still relevant.  There a few things that united as and that why we sub to list.  
1) Amiga
2) Blitz
3) Believes both of the above

Primary this list if for Blitz issues on the Amiga.  But that's now
look at the bigger picture.  Were is programming Amiga's going?   AI
have big plans for future of the Amiga's and so why don't we be just a
revolutionary as them.  Text based programming is yesterdays news. 
Programming should be very visual.  We if were no to careful on the
Amiga will be the only system that work in a Shell (CLI) environment
when programing.  What on if programming was like Workbench and still
have the ability of being still accessible from CLI like environment. 
That sounds like a very wacky idea.  But it shouldn't and most of us
have BBS (If not, why not?).  Now we can do this today, make it
realty.  A function the PC still don't have anything like is AREXX!

The GUI system would basically be front end that send the code to
blitz thought ARexx.  There are few things that have to be implicated
like contrail commanded instruction programmes database.  That
explains what each command douse and when each command is to be use. 

Think about for a moment.  I know a lot of you will hate my idea but
I don't care.  I see it as very good one, and one that should get
implicated.  But there is noway I would be able to do it all my self!

--
