could be next big thing on Aminet!  This would be good way of showing them 
on the Aminet that blitz is big news and that Blitz needs it own Directory!

--
What about Visual C?

Could be possible.  The idea is to make GUI that is not depend on Blitz but
communicates with Blitz thew ARexx.  Each new library for Blitz would need a
at least 2 files one contain all Visual Images (VI's) and one containing to Contrail
Commands (CC's).  All that would have to be change is the VI's and the
CC's. 

--
What about Visual AMOS?

What are you, mad something!  I can live with idea of C or E but AMOS, NO
GET LOST, get live please.  I will not embarrass you by giving out you
name.

--
Could I assign code to my Icon's to do certain events?

Thats the whole idea.  To simple to be true I know, but that simple.
IE.  And Icon that say that look like copyright simple © would ask you to
enter some details.  It would ask you for "Program name", "Author" and
"Date".  
Then it would write the code that would draw a window that say something like 
this

This Cool Progy
Copyright ME © 1998
Programmed on Amiga.
Complied on Blitz Basic.
Using Visual Blitz.

--
I wrought some code already with same sort of idea would be of any use?

YES, very much so.  But don't expect you code stay same for long.  I do not 
wont to see to versions coming out.  I won't only want to see one program 
using very best idea's.  

I will get in touch soon about mail-list.  I don't have money to log on and
run maillist my self (poor) but I bet we could find some who would help us
out. But early stages sorry to rest of you blitz mail-list will have to be
were we would have to talk.

The reason for that is because I don't think other Blitz use's on this
maillist want to know about this zxy Bug and should we or shouldn't we 
include a feature.

I wont people who are interested in Visual Blitz to be the one who decides
where it goes!

--
I not that a good programmer but like writing documents or drawing Icons?

Well you could be a key member.  Why programmes write bad manuals.  Don't
get me wrong but programmes are just to personally involved in program to
really explain the program.  Good example of this is Blitz Basic manuals.
They explain everything, but they explain nothing!  

On the subject of Icon's as said before this were we could final get draw
on Aminet. (Who's looking at you kid)

