@NODE "Mail.38" "Re: Tags and more"
	(envelope-from rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    14 Jul 98 09:42:37 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 1998 09:42:33 +0100
Subject: Re: Tags and more

On 10 Jul 98, at 16:58, Andreas Falkenhahn tippy-tappy-typed:

> Hi !
> 
> How can I set tags for RTRequest from Neils reqtools lib?
> I just want to set the tag #RT_LockWindow. How can I
> unlock it then?

 There is a .Tag (or TagItem) newtype in the amigalibs.res file. To use it, create and array 
of Tags (one longer than you will need - this last one should have contents of 0,0 and 
signals the end of the taglist).
 Put the tags into the array - rt_tags(0)\ti_Tag = #RT_LockWindow, <whatever data for tag 
is>
 When you call the function pass the address of first tag to use - &rt_tags(0).
 I think the window is unlocked one the requester is cleared, but I'm not sure.

And isn't there window (un)locking commands in that lib anyway? RTLockWindow and 
RTUnlockWindow.


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.



@ENDNODE
