@NODE "Mail.64" "sections"
From: "Paul West" <paul@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Date: 18 Jul 98 03:56:02 +0000
Subject: sections

hi

I was trying to convert a chunky-to-planar routine into blitz code,
spread accross a couple of statements.

The c2p routine is meant to be `blitter assisted' and has some code
for setting up a blitter queue and other stuff. That's not the
problem.

The problem is that the code wants to have a `chip section', ie a
section of the program that will be loaded into chipram, and it
accesses the location of this data by way of a label.

I take it blitz is not able to do sections in this way?

If not, how could I do it so that I could reserve a memory bank and
then have it located at a particular label? I have a grave feeling it
is not at all possible.

I do not know how the c2p works so I cannot really modify it. I am
only making it blitz compatible.

Any ideas?
Much appreciated.

--
Paul.

