ast )

>>In others words... a program that you can just "Click here and there" t=
o
make
>>what you want... with the all Blitz Flexiblity!

>>I can't wait to know how all of you think about this!
>>Roger


>Hi,

I would say "dont wast your time" doing this prpject. My excperianse
with these kind of programs are not very good. 9 out of 10 times the
code is very sloopy. Each programer structures his own programs in a
personal way. Using a program that generated a code for you would be
like getting a  source  code sent to you from a friend etc that uses
his  own   code  structuring, in this  case  your  structuring. It's
mipossible to write such a program  that will fit the liking of most
people etc, the only way would be to let the user config the program
how it's suppose to structure the output, and that is hard.

each programer also uses a  personal  style when they code. And then
there is the  fact that there are many 3rd  party librarys out there
and new gets written all the time, how would this be supported? Then
we have  speed. When  writing a  program  that generates a code, you =

will have to generate a code that is easy for eveyone to understand,
and that  means  not using  any tricks or  things like OS calls, ASM
routines etc, which many blitz programers use to make their programs
run faster and be more OS friendly.

I'm sorry but  I could go on, but I think I've made my point by now.
If you decide to  go  forward  with the project, then I wish you all
the best, and  hope that you  plan  it  very  carefull to make it as
configurable as possible to fit each  user. Why  not  add  a "learn"
mode  for  the  advanced users. With  this I mean, lets say  someone
wants to open a screen when he presses a button, now I'm pretty sure
that  when you generated  the code, it would use the SCREEN command.
Now some  ppl  might want to use OS  SCREENTAGS instead, so  why not
make it so that you can teach the program what YOU  want to use. And
why not add a  powerfull  plugin  message  port that  will let users
write plugins for  your program to give it even more power. Now with
powerfull I  mean, add  menus, popup, requesters, input gadgets that
pop up etc in the program.

 Bye!

