@NODE "Mail.80" "Re: Program code creator very easy to use"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Jul 1998 23:39:01 -0500
Subject: Re: Program code creator very easy to use

Hi Simon,

On 25-Jul-98, Simon Archer wrote:
> 
> But the idea behind most source creators is to do the donkey work for you.

Yes, exactly!  It used to take me hours of messing around, calculating, and
"trial-and-error" to make even a simple little window with GTGadgets and have
it come out the way I wanted.  Using GadToolsBox and a converter saves tons of
time and effort.  (I haven't tried yours, Simon, but it sounds better than the
one I've been using)

> I couldn't live without my source builders now. I used to do everything the
> hard way and code it all by hand. It took ages, now I can have a nice gui
> up and running within minutes. It's just a case of filling in the functions
> assigned to the different buttons.

I even save my functions, once written, and re-use them in other programs. 
Like for opening an ASL requester with a taglist, for example.  I just make
the original  with every concievable tag, then it's easy to optimize it for
the program at hand by cutting out the ones I don't need.

