@NODE "Mail.86" "Program code creator very easy to use"
Date: 25 Jul 98 16:52:38 GMT
X-Plug: Xenolink, No. 1 BBS Software for the Amiga!
From: bml@darkside.demon.co.uk (Simon Archer)
Subject: Program code creator very easy to use

On 24 Jul 98 Andreas =?iso-8859-1?Q?H=E5kansson? wrote about 'Program code
creator very easy to use'.

 Ai8> his  own   code  structuring, in this  case  your  structuring. It's
 Ai8> mipossible to write such a program  that will fit the liking of most
 Ai8> people etc, the only way would be to let the user config the program
 Ai8> how it's suppose to structure the output, and that is hard.

I tried as hard a sI could in BlitzGUIGen. It gives you the option of using
subroutines (Gosub) or statement/functions. Plus you can tell it to use
Select/Case loops or If/Then loops.

 Ai8> and that  means  not using  any tricks or  things like OS calls, ASM
 Ai8> routines etc, which many blitz programers use to make their programs
 Ai8> run faster and be more OS friendly.

But the idea behind most source creators is to do the donkey work for you.
There can never be a program that will write a program the way you want it,
because of the reasons you state. Source creators can only go so far to
give you a position in which to build on. MUIBuilder is another one.

I couldn't live without my source builders now. I used to do everything the
hard way and code it all by hand. It took ages, now I can have a nice gui
up and running within minutes. It's just a case of filling in the functions
assigned to the different buttons.

Simon Archer




