@NODE "Mail.87" "Problem with my proggy"
Date: Fri, 31 Jul 1998 10:25:26 -0500
From: Bohdan Lechnowsky <bohdan_lechnowsky@csgsystems.com>
Subject: Problem with my proggy

Below I have attached a copy of a recent CLI program I wrote to rip HREF
links from an HTML file.  I works fine on my A3000/040@25 (most of the
time), but on WinUAE0.6.9 it locks after outputting the last line
*almost* every time.  This is also what happens on the A3000 the few
times it hasn't worked.

Does anyone know of any reason why this would happen?

-Bo

P.S.  Please feel free to compile, modify and use the source code for
your own purposes.  If you make it better, please send me a copy :^)

P.P.S.  Sorry for sending this via Netscape mail...I'm at work :^(

P.P.P.S.  In looking at the code right now (I can't get Blitz 2.1 to
work on UAE, Ted's fonts are like 1 or 2 points in size--unreadable) I'm
wondering if I have to send FileInput back to the console...but you'd
think this would cause it to never work on the A3000 or UAE.

=====================================================================
;This is BB2.1 source code to extract HREF links from an HTML file
WBStartup
;NoCli

If NumPars<>1
  NPrint "Usage: BHREFind <filename>"
EndIf
Filename1$=Par$(1)    ;This is the name of the file to search for links

Dim linklist$(1024)   ;This is the maximum number of links findable in a
file

CaseSense Off         ;This command is needed for "instr" command to
follow
k=0                   ;This variable holds the number of links found
FileNum1=1
If ReadFile(FileNum1,Filename1$)
  FileInput FileNum1
  While NOT Eof(FileNum1)
    inline$=Edit$(512)
    href=Instr(inline$,"href")
    If href>0

      ;This section find the beginning and ending of the link
      ; even if it is on different lines

      break=0
      p=Instr(inline$,"=",href)
      p1=Instr(inline$,Chr$(34),p+3)
      If p1=0
        inline2$=Edit$(512)
        p1=Instr(inline2$,Chr$(34))
        break=1
      EndIf

      ;This section assembles the link into a variable string named
linky$
      ; and removes leading and trailing spaces and quotes

      If break=0
        linky$=StripLead$(StripTrail$(Mid$(inline$,p+1,p1-p-1),32),32)
      EndIf
      If break=1
       
linky$=StripLead$(StripTrail$(Mid$(inline$,p+1,Len(inline$)-p),32),32)
       
linky$=linky$+StripLead$(StripTrail$(Left$(inline2$,p1-1),32),32)
        inline$=inline2$
        inline2$=""
      EndIf
      linky$=StripLead$(StripTrail$(linky$,34),34)

      ;This section filters out the different types of HREFs
      ; i.e. Mailto, HTTP, FTP, etc.

      If UCase$(Left$(linky$,7))="MAILTO:"
        linky$=""
      EndIf
      If UCase$(Left$(linky$,4))="FTP:"
        linky$=""
      EndIf
      If (UCase$(Left$(linky$,5))<>"HTTP:") AND (Len(linky$)>0)
        linky$="/"+linky$
      EndIf
      k=k+1
      linklist$(k)=linky$

      ;This section checks for duplicate links on this page

      duplicate=0
      If k>1
        For l=1 To k-1
          If (linklist$(k)=linklist$(l)) OR
("/"+linklist$(k)=linklist$(l))
            linklist$(k)=""
            k=k-1
            duplicate=1
            l=k           ;This sets the loop var to the end of the
                          ; loop (i.e. exit loop)
          EndIf
        Next
      EndIf

      ;This section outputs the link if it isn't a duplicate

      If (duplicate=0) AND (Len(linky$)>0)
        NPrint linklist$(k)
      EndIf
    EndIf
  Wend
EndIf
CloseFile FileNum1

End



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.88" "Re: Problem with my proggy"
	(envelope-from rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    31 Jul 98 16:34:36 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Fri, 31 Jul 1998 16:34:29 +0100
Subject: Re: Problem with my proggy

On 31 Jul 98, at 10:25, Bohdan Lechnowsky gave this nugget of information:

> P.P.P.S.  In looking at the code right now (I can't get Blitz 2.1 to
> work on UAE, Ted's fonts are like 1 or 2 points in size--unreadable) I'm
> wondering if I have to send FileInput back to the console...but you'd
> think this would cause it to never work on the A3000 or UAE.

 Well, you should do a PopInput to return the CLI to the way it was, 
i.e:

If ReadFile(#,"blah")
  FileInput #
  ...
  blah
  ...
  PopInput
  CloseFile #
End If


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.
|rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk|



@ENDNODE
