Hi Blitzers.

the following is an example on how to create AppIcons I found in the BSS.=
 The
problem is that the 'PortSigBit' command causes a system crash on 68000/6=
8010
machines. Is there anyone who knows how I can use the 'AddWaitEvent' comm=
and
without 'PortSigBit'?

Thank you in advance for helping.



----------

  ;Example usage of AppIcons
  ;
  ; .-------------------------.
  ; | RI AppLibrary EXAMPLE 1 |
  ; `-------------------------'
  ;
  ; Example usage of AppIcons
  ; Uses new commands AddWaitEvent from windowslib
  ;      and PortSigBit from RIMiscLib
  ;      and EZRequest from RIMiscLib
  ;
  ; Drag Files onto the AppIcon to see what happens
  ; To QUIT, simply double-click the AppIcon

  #IDCMP_BOOPSI=3D$800000   ; or use the resident Blitzlibs:amigalibs.res=


  NoCli
  WBenchToFront_
  FindScreen 0,"Workbench"  ; a good way of finding the Workbench screen
  ShowScreen 0
  Use Screen 0

  If AddAppIcon(0,"AppTest","SYS:Disk")
    EZRequest "AppExample1","Please drag some files onto the 'AppTest'
icon,|or double-click it to Quit","Okey Dokey"
    AddWaitEvent PortSigBit(AppMsgPort),#IDCMP_BOOPSI
    quitflag.b=3D0
    Repeat
      ev.l=3DWaitEvent
      Select ev
        Case #IDCMP_BOOPSI
          If AppEvent     ; make sure it really is an AppEvent
            Select AppEventType
              Case 2
                For n=3D1 To AppNumFiles
                  EZRequest "AppExample1","File number "+Str$(n)+" is
:|"+AppFile(n),"Thats Interesting"
                Next n
                If AppNumFiles=3D0 Then quitflag=3D-1
              End Select
            End Select
          EndIf
    Until quitflag
    EZRequest "AppExample1","I shall quit now|Thanks for watching","I won=
t
forget it"
    DelAppIcon 0
  Else
    EZRequest "AppExample1","I am unable to create the AppIcon for you","=
Never
mind"
  EndIf


-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

