    16 Jul 98 09:07:09 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 1998 09:06:57 +0100
Subject: Re: Pack&Unpack little files

On 8 Jan 98, at 20:20, Krzysiek Jonko tippy-tappy-typed:

> I've wrote small program to "pack" many little files into a big one.
> I've a little SEEK procedure to get desired file but...
> Look at the included example: when I "pack" any files (ie. included two
> pictures IFF16) and unpack them again - the files are corrupted. WHY?
> Program is quite simpe - I really don't understand it... Can anybody tell
> me what I'm doing wrong?

 It works fine on my machine (A1200, HD, CD). I did change your source but I 
don't think that would have had much impact. Anyway, what I changed was this:

PackRX.bb2: I didn't have the correct libs, so I hard-coded the DIR$= and 
PRG$= lines (I assumed they would be ProgDir$ and ProgName$). Also the 
second part of the ChDir DIR$ line, I couldn't figure out what it was so I removed 
it completely. I also changed the CLR.l d2 to a MOVEQ.l #0,d2 (for no 
particular reason).


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.
|rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk|



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.99" "Pack&Unpack little files"
