@NODE "Mail.114" "Re: OS friendly double buffering"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 1998 16:20:42 -0500
Subject: Re: OS friendly double buffering

Hi Jake,

On 08-Jan-78, Jake Frederick wrote:
> I am trying to write an OS friendly game but am having trouble with the
double
> buffering. Please tell me what I am missing in the following blitting
routine.
> The screen flickers when it is executed.
> 
I am assuming you have your two bitmaps #and buffers set up as 0 and #1?  If
not, I don't think your code will work.  Other than that, it looks right.


> ShowBitMap buf
> buf=1-buf
> VWait
> Use Bitmap buf
> Unbuffer buf
> bblit buf,z,x,y

Here is my code, which does work with no flickering.  But it is functionally
the same as yours.

.Draw              ;double buffer drawing routine
  ShowBitMap see        ;show the already-drawn page
  VWait                 ;wait for the Vblank
  Use BitMap draw       ;now draw on the unseen page
  UnBuffer draw         ;erase the stuff we drew last time
  BBlit draw,shp,sx,sy  ;buffer-blit specified shape
  Exchange see,draw     ;make this the new viewing page
Return


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/





@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.115" "OS friendly double buffering"
From: Jake Frederick <gonzo@acadia.net>
Date: Sun, 08 Jan 1978 18:41:55 +0500
Subject: OS friendly double buffering

I am trying to write an OS friendly game but am having trouble with the double
buffering. Please tell me what I am missing in the following blitting routine.
The screen flickers when it is executed.

ShowBitMap buf
buf=1-buf
VWait
Use Bitmap buf
Unbuffer buf
bblit buf,z,x,y


