@NODE "Mail.129" "Re[2]: NewLibrarySet V1.10"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 1998 22:11:21 +0100
Subject: Re[2]: NewLibrarySet V1.10

    Hi Paul, =


> I was wondering though, how did you do your masking?

    The masking is only present in the NChunkyBlit command and is pretty =
easy
(and slow BTW :-(). I move the shape byte per byte and check if the colou=
r is
0 or not. If it's 0, I don't copy the byte to the chunky buffer. These
routines was written pretty fast and I know that we could do it better. B=
ut
the NChunkyBlock4 seems to be the fastest routine available.
 =

> Any benchmarks as to how the routines perform?

    Oki :)

    My config is an A1230/50, 16 Mb.

    ChunkyBuffer and shapes are in FAST memory ! I've take a 16*16 chunky=

block for all the testing. Maximum blit for 1 VWAit (Pal mode-50hz)

    NChunkyBlit  : 140 Blits (with transparent)
    NChunkyBlock2: 310 Blits (no transparent)
    NChunkyBlock4: 550 Blits (no transparent)

    You can use the NChunkyBlock4 to blit more than 2 320*200 shapes in l=
ess
than 1 VWait!

    Cool ? :)

    If any other questions...

    For now,

        Fred

PS: I've almost finished the new ASL library. It's 1000 times better than=
 the
old Blitz one :-). =

