 K6-233MHz-32MB-4,3GB-24X-Voodoo




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.134" "Re: NewLibraries"
From: Jarmo Laakkonen <jami@dlc.fi>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 1998 22:49:58 +0200
Subject: Re: NewLibraries

Andreas Etzrodt wrote something like this:

> am I wrong when I say that the NewLibrarySet
> (or its lib#) collides with BSS?

Get a small tool I wrote from aminet.
dev/basic/ChangeLibNum.lha

-- 
Bye..
Jarmo Laakkonen
jami@dlc.fi




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.135" "Re: NewLibraries"
From: Rui de Carvalho <grim@esoterica.pt>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 1998 18:22:24 +0100
Subject: Re: NewLibraries

Hello Andreas

On 22-Jul-98, Andreas Etzrodt wrote:
> Hello,

> am I wrong when I say that the NewLibrarySet
> (or its lib#) collides with BSS?

> Window lib collides with RInonvolatile lib (35)
> Screen lib collides with RIfastserial lib (36)
> String lib collides with RIgtmenu lib (37)

> It there something I can do for this?

> Bye, =

> Andy

This is correct, there is that conflict. =

I deleted those libs and recompiled DefLibs.(I didn't used them anyway)


Best Regards
