X-Software: Aweb, Miami, Thor, ScalOS, MCP and assorted bits of bytes...
X-UIN: 12427044
X-Misc-info: Who's reading this??

Frédéric Laboureur (alphasnd@hol.fr) wrote:

>    The NewCommandsSet series continue and now the GadTools library is
>supported ! Menus/Gadgets are easy to create and the result is impressive.
>You can expect an under 6kb exec for a fully gadtools guided software. 

Hm. This release is the first one I've tried and so far...no luck I'm
afraid. I get it installed correctly but not even the examples
provided will work. Or simple tries I've done myself for that matter.

dr.l=NWbToScreen(0)

Should work shouldn't it? I get a syntax error if I try that one.

---
I've got better things to do than argue with every wrong-headed
crackpot with an ignorant opinion! I'm a busy man! _I_ say, either
agree with me or take a hike! I'm right, period! End of discussion!
