@NODE "Mail.145" "Re: New manual!"
 Sat, 18 Jul 1998 20:05:06 +0100 (BST)
 <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Sat, 18 Jul 1998 09:37:32 -0500 (CDT)
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 1998 09:35:20 +0500
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Subject: Re: New manual!

On 17-Jul-98, Andre Beer flashed:
>Hi Nick!

>I'm interested in such a manual. But does not Donovan Reeve (also on this
>list) already write on a new manual?


  I am still working on a new manual for Blitz which is intended to lay the
groundwork for the manual for Pheonix (a Blitz replacement).  Work has not
progressed very far due to a number of factors mostly beyond my control.
This is intended to be a very in-depth work which will include concise and
lucid explaination and examples which will be helpful to users at all levels.
The plan is to involve the Blitz community in generating complete and
accurate information on not only all the official Blitz features and bugs,
but all useful third-party add-ons as well.  This project in its Blitz
incarnation will likely be an evolving freeware electronic text, preferably
in a hyperbook style such as AmigaGuide.  It will be some time however
before it becomes very useful to the Blitz coder.

  I would be highly in favor of another person going ahead with a new Blitz
manual for several reasons:

  - They may well have a very different focus and method.

  - They may well have a different level of presentation.

  - Having more than one explaination of commands is often helpful.

  - One may have information on things not covered by the other.

  - I am a perfectionist and take a long time to do things.

  - Unless I get a lot of help, the workload is going to delay me a lot.

  - The manual at the moment must be a "spare time" project with me.

  I will probably release my manual on a section-by section basis with
each release containing all of the info of previous releases plus
whatever new info has been added.



  So if "tri" wants to make a manual. I say go for it!  I would like to
see that happen and will be in line to buy one along with everyone else.
The value as a reference work will be well worth the price range mentioned.



catcha later,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)





