@NODE "Mail.156" "Re: My executable crashing..."
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 1998 06:46:54 -0500
Subject: Re: My executable crashing...

Hi Luca

On 15-Jul-98, Luca Ferraris wrote:
> 
> A little question about a strange crashing appearing when my game's
> executable is launched under ks.1.3 or 2.0/2.04 (not tested under 2.1).
> 
> I have an A1200 with Blizzard 1230IV+FPU and on my Amiga the executable
> works properly.
> Testing it on an A500 Plus (2.0) and on A500 with kickstart 1.3, it seems 
> to crash at the beginning, when the main program has been just loaded in
> memory.
> 
> The question is: have you got some ideas about this strange thing???
> Is there some Blitz library working only with OS 3.0 or working only with
> higher processors (68020+)?

My first thought would be that you don't have enough chip memory available on
the A500's.  Have you checked your program to see how much chip ram it
requires?
And how much fast ram?

An A500 has at best 1M chip available, and some only 1/2M.  If the 500 has no
fast ram, ALL the code & variables must share this chip ram too.

Once you know how much memory your program requires, you can put a check in
the beginning to see if there is enough available on the user's machine before
loading any graphics, sounds, etc.  And if not, the program could put up a
requester to let the user know what the problem is, and exit instead of
crashing. 

Later...
-- 
Desk: A wastebin with drawers.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
