@NODE "Mail.168" "miscellaneous questions"
 Sun, 19 Jul 1998 21:54:47 +0100 (BST)
 netsoc.ucd.ie!blitz-list; Sun, 19 Jul 1998 22:52:12 +0200
 Sun, 19 Jul 1998 22:47:56 +0200
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 1998 16:49:29 +0200
From: philippe.bovier@ramses.frmug.org (Philippe Bovier)
Subject: miscellaneous questions

Hello,

-   We  have  released  our  De-Archiveur  in  Aminet  (De-Archiveur13.lha
util/pack  93ko).   It's  a  gui  for  LHA,LZX,DMS,ZIP,etc...   written in
BlitzBasic2.   You  can  also manipulate one or more file in an archive or
convert an archive LHA-> LZX for example.

Maybe  It  can  be usefull for you and If you have time you can use it and
send me your comment, bugs report or improvement or anything else. Use the
adress at the end of the mail.

Now some questions:


- De-Archiveur is programmed in Blitz Mode and It used Shapes for his GUI.
Our XFD GUI Package (and principally the XFD PATCH GUI is programmed with
the systeme for having the shortest exe as possible (and also to learn how
programming in systeme mode).

We  have  no  idea to use the same shape than the one used in De-Archiveur
(bitz mode) in XFD PATCH GUI (system mode).  How can we used a shape in a
program in system mode ?????  (little source welcome if possible).



- Filefrog is a program like dopus4 or filemaster. It look like very great
(hello jean). I'm now a A1500T with a PIV and the video option ad now I can
use PIV mode. Filefrog used only one mode (PAL:HIRES). too bad :-(

How can we used a screenrequester to choose a screen mode and how can we
adapt the GUI with all the differents modes available ??? (Filefrog is
completely programmed in system mode).



- I'm the gfx artist of BubbleBobble AGA. I'm always wanted to make an AGA
version of BubbleBobble. The GFX are in 128 colors and all are shapes untill
now. Like others persons, we encountered problems with speed for the games
and actually look after solutions about that. I send mail about this problem
in this Blitz ML and received responses but It's not easy for us because
it's our first game. (we know more about utility). It's sure I decode example
you send in this ML about cpu blitting or interleaved bitmap and I encourage
someone to released in Aminet a very good archive with plenty of example or
better a nex lib for the Blitz. A support for gfx card are welcome.

Finally the last question (for me :-) )

- How much colors can I take in the Dpaint palette to transform some gfx
in sprite (principal hero, shoot or options) to gain some speed ???

- There is special place in the Dpaint palette for the sprite colors??



Philippe Bovier ( *Mrod* ) #E-MAIL#: Philippe.Bovier@ramses.telis-sc.fr
