@NODE "Mail.173" "Re: memtypes"
From: Dave Newton <Dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 03 Jul 1998 15:36:34 -0000
Subject: Re: memtypes


Hi alex,

 Well the memtypes are the standard allocmem types, used by the os, and
the blitz command. Here are the ones I use,

#MEMCLEAR=$10000;to clear the allocated memory
#MEMFAST=$4;to force fast memory to be used only
#MEMCHIP=$2;to force chip memory to be used only
#MEMPUBLIC=$1;no virtual mem please

If you use MEMFAST, beware as if there isn't any fast on that machine,
it will not allocate any. If you don't specify MEMFAST or MEMCHIP, it
will attempt to allocate fast memory first, then chip memory. Here's
what I use

MakeBitmap{0,320,256,8,#MEMCLEAR|#MEMFAST|#MEMPUBLIC} ;FASTMEM ONLY
MakeBitmap{0,320,256,8,#MEMCLEAR|#MEMCHIP|#MEMPUBLIC};CHIPMEM ONLY
MakeBitmap{0,320,256,8,#MEMCLEAR|#MEMPUBLIC};ANYMEM TYPE


Hope that helps,

Dave.

P.s. I've seen the example...that should work, unless it's something to
do with the blitz display lib. I'll try and see if it's my routines messing
it up. I'll try it in a screen to see if it works. You should use clearmem
though to allocate your bitmaps though.

