@NODE "Mail.188" "Re: Libraries problem"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Wed, 29 Jul 1998 16:23:31 +0100
Subject: Re: Libraries problem

    Hi Chris, =


> My problem  is in BLITZ executable files.
> When I compile program SOME Amiga libraries are opened BEFORE running
> first line of program. For example datatypes.library - if you even woul=
d
> like to check if datatypes are available on your machine - you can't do=

> that. BLITZ executable required datatypes.library :-(
> Try to run SnoopDOS and rename datatypes.libray in LIBS: to explain my
> problem.
> But some libraries are opened only when you run some functions from
> them (example: identify library).
> Is there any way to ommit this problem?

    This is to avoid this problem than I've written the NewCommandSet too=
=2E
Each new libraries call in 'standard' blitz2 command do it like you have =
said,
before the first code line. If a library is missing, the program stop to =
load
until it find the library (an endless loop). In the NewCommandSet, each
library which need to be opened (diskfont, gadtools, asl, ..) can be chec=
ked
via the NInitXxx command.

    There is no way to prevent that. Sorry.

        Fred.

