@NODE "Mail.198" "Jimi"
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Tue, 28 Jul 1998 14:56:01 +1200
Subject: Jimi

On 28-Jul-98, Paul West wrote:
>Fred,

>>     I've got your c2p package but the 030 routine doesn't compile :(.
>It seems
>> to be the Jimi commands which isn't recognized by my Blitz2 compiler
>(version
>> 1.7). It's tokenized but it say 'Syntax Error'. What is this Jimi
>function ?
>> I've replaced it with RTS but it seems to not be the same (program
>crahs)
>> If you have any suggestions...

>Well well. I have no idea what a Jimi function is either. I will have
>a look....
 
  It's Jimi as in Hendrix :-)  There is (or was) several undocumented
functions with silly names like that :) 
  They do things like, instead of writing a=a+1 (or a+1) you write 
`Jimi a' - just for the hell of it :-)

