        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz> ICQ #15349462
    




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.199" "Re: JIMI"
From: "Paul West" <paul@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Date: 29 Jul 98 19:45:38 +0000
Subject: Re: JIMI

> What version of Blitz do you own?
> I think these features can be found in Blitz Suport Suite. 
> 
> On my Blitz you can also find:

I think mine is just normal blitz 2.1. I got it just prior to the cd
version being released.
 
>     * BERT

That might be assembler but I don't think so because Bcc condition
codes are usually only two characters.

>     * BIGBIRD (They forgot Miss Piggy)

Definately for fun that one.

>     * 5 diferent JIMI (I think they are a family of illegal aliens that are
> entering
>       your country through Blitz)

Must be.

>     * ORI

Or immediate. It's assembler. It means that the data which follows
immediately after the instruction is to be used in a logical or
operation on a destination data.

>     * PEA

That's assembler too, push effective address. I never use it though so
I don't altogether know what it does. Something to do with the stack.
similar to LEA (load effective address) but stack-related.

>     * NANA

No ideas.

-- 
Paul.

