@NODE "Mail.213" "I can code VisualBasic."
From: Jon Lennart Berg <aniwiese@online.no>
Date: Wed, 01 Apr 1998 21:42:15 +0100
Subject: I can code VisualBasic.

Hi blitzers.

For the past year i have been experimenting with writing my own
GUI systems, using assembler and BlitzBasic.
A few years back, i also created a script-compiler.

If enough people want to, i can tie these two elements together,
and effectivly create VisualBasic.
Its actualy not as hard as people think. Its heavy coding, lotsa
pointers and taglists, but the result would be good.

The only problem, as far as i know, is that you cant use BLINK on
blitzbasic code. There is no way to link referenced datas to
the main executable (this can be done in c,e and even hisoft basic).

But you would get a very easy system.

Tell me if any are interested, it would ofcource be free...




