@NODE "Mail.214" "I can code VisualBasic."
Date: 25 Jul 98 16:04:25 GMT
X-Plug: Xenolink, No. 1 BBS Software for the Amiga!
From: bml@darkside.demon.co.uk (Simon Archer)
Subject: I can code VisualBasic.

On 21 Jul 98 Cox, Michael D wrote about 'I can code VisualBasic.'.

 CMD> I would be very interested.  My biggest problem is always creating the
 CMD> Interface.  If I could draw the interface, give the gadgets names and
 CMD> then write code for when they are Clicked or Changed or Selected, that
 CMD> would make life so much easier.

I take it you've never tried the Gadtoolsbox 2.0c / BlitzGUIGen combination?

It doesn't get much easier than that. Both programs are available from
Aminet, and the resultant code from BlitzGUIGen is really easy to follow.
Full commenting and program flow, making it child's work to create even the
best
looking Gadtools GUI's. And if you register BlitzGUIGen, it allows a host
of even more sophisticated components like window backfills etc.


A note to the few that commented about the arrival of GadToolsBox 3.0. I
will
not be updating BlitzGUIGen to use this latest version until GTB becomes stable
enough. I can't say I'm too keen on the idea of the custom gadgets etc anyway.
Bubblehelp, registers etc would be time consuming and probably fairly
slow in Blitz anyhow, as they would have to be custom written.

Simon Archer




@ENDNODE
