@NODE "Mail.217" "Hi! ("
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie
	id 0z0aRy-0004Wm-00; Mon, 27 Jul 1998 00:43:35 +0100
From: Thomas Newsom <thomas.newsom@allhours.karoo.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 26 Jul 1998 10:07:30 +0100
Subject: Hi! (

Hi there!,

I've just joined this list so forgive me if I ask something someone has
recently asked about Blitz2. I've been using BB2 (registered) for a few years
on and off, recently returning to it. I've lost a lot of my extra tools and
old code when we moved house :( So....

Is there a tool anywhere that allows one to turn C header files into something
easily used in BB2?

Can I turn a C header file into a NEWTYPE and then pass the NEWTYPE to a
library fucntion call? If so how? Something like this...

NEWTYPE.ramstruct
  name$              ;          /* name of user On this port                 
*/
  Baud_Rate.l        ;          /* users baud rate                           
*/
  Command_Stack$     ;          /* storage for command stack while switching 
*/
  Local_Flag$        ;          /* user is logged in locally                 
*/
  Action$            ;          /* users current action                      
*/
  amodule$           ;          /* module number user in in                  
*/
  area.b             ;          /* area number user is in (msg or file)      
*/
  CLI$               ;          /* cli process number                        
*/
  menu$              ;          /* menu name they left the MENU module using 
*/
  DefAction$         ;          /* default action for current menu           
*/
  chainflag$         ;          /* used internally                           
*/
  status.l           ;          /* See below                                 
*/
  suspended.w        ;          /* time clock suspended                      
*/
  time_left.b        ;          /* time left when suspended                  
*/
  suspd_adj.b        ;          /* online time adjustment                    
*/
  unused$            ;          /* not used                                  
*/
End NEWTYPE

How would I pass that to a function call so the function fills in the NEWTYPE
for later use?

Whats the official BB2 url?

Is there an FTP Blitz site anywhere (apart from aminet)?

Where is the best place on the net to get libraries (apart from aminet)?

All information greatfully received.

Cheers
-- 
Tom.

AKA The Jeepster - Gagged but never silent - MEMBER <:> *Team AMIGA*
Email : Jeepster@allhours.karoo.co.uk <-> Fido : 2:2502/61.0 & 2:2502/59.0




@ENDNODE
