@NODE "Mail.219" "Here's a Great blitz2 tip!"
From: Jon Lennart Berg <aniwiese@online.no>
Date: Fri, 03 Apr 1998 21:42:14 +0100
Subject: Here's a Great blitz2 tip!

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.

This message was composed on an Amiga using the YAM mailer.
YAM is available at http://bitcom.ch/~mbeck/

--BOUNDARY.7397.724.133500464.1


Did you ever wanted to clip text inside an area of a window?
Well, every window has a rectangle definition that controls this!
This letter includes a short example on how to do it.

It saves memory as well, just open a normal window (not $400), then
set the clip area, and text/gfx will not override the window borders.

Hope you guys like it
Jon Lennart Berg
--BOUNDARY.7397.724.133500464.1

#Attachment stripped# 

--BOUNDARY.7397.724.133500464.1--

@ENDNODE
