@NODE "Mail.225" "GTLV_ShowSelected problem solved"
	Fri, 3 Jul 1998 17:10:58 +0100 (BST)
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 1998 17:10:58 +0100
From: Adam Lounds <adaml@tcp.net.uk>
Subject: GTLV_ShowSelected problem solved

Hi Y'all

You may recall that a few days ago I had a problem with 
GTLV_ShowSelected and turning it off!

Well, after further investivation, it appears that it
is not possible to do this using GTSetAttrs, it 
has to be set before the list is shown using GTSetTags.

A solution was found, though - 

as part of the mousehit routine (to check buttons etc after
a mouse click), I detected if the listview was hit in the normal
way. When a hit was detected, I did a
GTSetAttrs #Win, #LV, #GTLV_Selected,-1

which tells Intuition that the selected item is not visible. 
Voila! A non-permanent bar!

Hope this helps someone!

regards,
-- 
Adam Lounds                     | Email: adaml@tcp.net.uk
Network Assistant               | Tel: +44 1703 571300
Total Connectivity Providers    | WWW: http://www.tcp.co.uk/



@ENDNODE
