@NODE "Mail.230" "Games on gfx-boards"
From: Andreas Etzrodt <the_shark@gmx.de>
Date: Thu, 09 Jul 1998 12:41:10 +0100
Subject: Games on gfx-boards

Hello,

I want to write a game. This game has to work on gfx-boards, too.
But I don't have any experience in programming games or at least
do some gfx-stuff with blitz basic. 

At the moment I open a screen with a taglist. Then I load an
iff-image into a bitmap and copy it with bitmaptowindow to my
screen (of course there is a window on this screen) as a
backdrop-picture. 

This works fine. Now I want to use something like sprites/bobs/shapes
wich I can control with a joypad. Which commands do I need to use?

I mean, if I blit a shape onto the screen it will stay there. And if
it moves it will just be blitted again and again. But how do I 
remove the "old" images? -> blit -> remove -> blit on other position.

Bye, 
 Andy
