On 18-Jul-98, Centro Amiga coffed up:
>Hya

>> I want to write some game editors for my game.
>> The last ones I did weren't OS and actually slowed
>> my development down!
>> =

>> So now I'm going for OS but I noticed that the Screen
>> command only allows for 64 colours. This is not good
>> because I need 256 colours.

Yeah, the screen command can use any of the AGA depths.
Maybe you have not used the command properly or you =

need to use all the parameters for the command. Like...

  Screen 0,0,0,320,256,_8_,$0000,"An 256 colour screen",1,2

That should work, cos Im sure I've used it before... hummm

Anthony Sherratt

