@NODE "Mail.247" "Re: Font sizes / GT Menus"
	(envelope-from rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    31 Jul 98 09:14:17 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Fri, 31 Jul 1998 09:14:10 +0100
Subject: Re: Font sizes / GT Menus

On 31 Jul 98, at 5:00, Blitzwing gave this nugget of information:

> 1) How Can I check the fonts being used by Workbench

 If you're only wanting the screen font (menus, window titles, 
screen titles etc) as opposed to the icon font or default CLI font, 
then you can do this.

Wbtoscreen 0
*myscreen.Screen = peek.l(addr screen(0))
fontname$ = peek$(*myscreen\Font\Name)
fontsize.w = *myscreen\Font\YSize

 Check the names for the subfields of the .Screen type by going to 
the View Newtypes menu item - but they should be right.

> 2) How do I access GT menus (normal menus are *really* ugly)

 Use the RIGTMenuLib or use the OS commands. If you use the 
RIGTMenuLib, then only the definitions of your menus/items 
change - simply put GT in front of the Menu/Item/SubItem 
commands. The window processing loop 
(WaitEvent...MenuHit/ItemHit/etc) are all the same.


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.
|rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk|



@ENDNODE
