@NODE "Mail.260" "Re: Fade"
          Fri, 24 Jul 1998 08:51:47 +0200
          Fri, 24 Jul 1998 08:51:41 +0200 (MET DST)
From: Damir Arh <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
Date: Fri, 24 Jul 1998 08:49:39 +0100
Subject: Re: Fade

On 23-Jul-98, Andreas Etzrodt wrote:

> Hello,
> 
> is it somehow possible to do a fadein or fadeout in AmigaMode?
> 
> The commands "FadeIn" and "FadeOut" seem to be very handy but
> only work in Blitz-Mode.
> 
> I want to display a picture, fade it out (fade to black) and
> fade the new one in onto the screen (fade from black).

Here is a routine I use in my game (it should also answer Andreas
Falkenhahn's 'Faaaaast fading' question):

  Statement Fade{}
    For i=1 To 100
      FadePalette 1,1,0.98
      Use Palette 1
      VWait
    Next i
  End Statement

Of course you should currently use Palette 1. After you call the function,
you have a black screen, you should now CLS and change the bitmap to what
you want. I don't use fading in, but you should be able to write a similar
function with reversed functionality.

Regards
-- 
