@NODE "Mail.263" "Re: Faaaaast fading"
From: "Steven Wojciechowski" <stevie-woj@boy-woj.demon.co.uk>
Date: 28 Jul 98 00:35:26 +0100
Subject: Re: Faaaaast fading

Previously in Life Andreas Falkenhahn(Andreas.Falkenhahn@mail.regio.net) had this to say:
> How to gain a faster fade on a bitmap with depth 8?
> If I fade every colour from 0 to its value its sloooow!!!
> I need it faster! Any idea?
> 

I don't know how to speed up the fading code but you could try fading
the colours in 3 or 4 groups.  ie. 1st frame fade colours 0 - 63 next
frame fade 64 - 127, next frame 128 - 191, next frame 192 - 255, then
next frame go back to colours 0 - 63.  this way might look strange for
*very* short fades, but should look ok if fading is to take a second
or 2.

Off hand thats the only way I can think of but there are probably
other tricks you could use as well.  Hope it helps anyway.

--
Stevie W. 
http://www.boy-woj.demon.co.uk/
stevie-woj@boy-woj.demon.co.uk



