> off your caches! 

Yes, check your SetPatch.  I recently had all sorts of strange, seemingly
unrelated problems that turned out to be due to an old SetPatch that some
piece of software installed without checking the version number.

This included some programs crashing on exit, some crashing on startup, and
some running OK but with various functions not working, or causing alerts or
crashes. Strangest of all was that the 68020 and the 68040 versions of Ppaint
would run fine, but the 68030 version would crash. (I have a 68030) 

All problems were fixed when I replaced the right SetPatch command.
> 
Later...

