Hi Dave,

Thanks for your advice, I now seem to have found the reason for the messup
(touch wood): It seems that the CHIP bitmap width has to be in multiples of
64!
When I increased the CHIP bitmap width to 384 (and other multiples of 64) it
suddenly displayed perfectly!  Is this because it suited your particular
game?  I don`t think the extra width is a problem yet, as I just ignore the
extra width and carry on, but its still early days, I don`t know what effect
it will have later on.

The only problem I found was the speed of it, its sloooow! I remember a
couple of days back you said that you were using a faster system that
