Date: 20 Jul 98 17:12:08 +0000
Subject: Re: CopList, Smoothscroll....

> 2) Is it possible to open a highres Interlace (640x512x8) CopList?
>     If it`s possible, which parameters do I need to use?  

Somebody posted code for this just recently using an interrupt.

You're not actually supposed to use an interrupt though, you're meant
to have an instruction at the end of your first copperlist moving the
location of the second one into the copperlist-program-counter, and
vice versa for the second frame. In interlace there are two
copperlists usually you see.

--
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.283" "Re: Console"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 1998 19:49:24 -0500
Subject: Re: Console 

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1748162216.2

Hi Damir,

On 18-Jul-98, Damir Arh wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> How caan I open a console? I'd like to print some info there before actually
> loading the game and I don't want my game to be runnable from CLI only. (I
> want to print to something like DefaultOutput, which causes a crash if the
> game is ran from WB.)

DefaultOutput will cause a crash in a WB started program, because there is no
place for the output to go. 

Try this attached example instead.  

Later...
-- 
I haven't lost my mind; it's backed up on tape somewhere.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748162216.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="ConsoleWindow"

WBStartup
NoCli
WBenchToFront_
FindScreen 0

DosBuffLen 0        ;needed to force immediate output to the "file"

If WriteFile (0,"CON:0/50//100/TEST/CLOSE")
  FileOutput 0
  NPrint "Just a test"
  VWait 20
  MouseWait
  CloseFile 0
Else
  BeepScreen 0      ;something went wrong!
EndIf

End



--BOUNDARY.1748162216.2--





@ENDNODE
