@NODE "Mail.286" "Re: Confused..."
          Thu, 9 Jul 1998 08:48:26 +0200
          Thu, 9 Jul 1998 08:48:18 +0200 (MET DST)
From: Damir Arh <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
Date: Thu, 09 Jul 1998 08:47:52 +0100
          http://www.yam.ch
Subject: Re: Confused...

Hello Michael

On 06-Jul-98, you wrote:

> Hi all.
> Ok, say I wanted to convert a BLITZ mode proggy into an AMIGA mode =

> system friendly one. The BLITZ code uses the display lib, Blits and
> BBlits. =


In this case there shouldn't be any problems in the BLITZ to AMIGA
conversion. I've done a similar thing some time ago with my game.

> All the posts I have read on this list to do with system friendly image=
 =

> stuff seem to be harping on about fastram bitmaps, cpu blits, cpu scrol=
ls =

> and all manner of bits and pieces such as graphics cards etc...
> Arrrgghhh!!! =


Just don't get confused with all this, you don't need to use it, if you
don't want to.

> I may have missed all the answers in previous posts, but can anyone giv=
e =

> info on the bestest/fastest ways to get bitmaps and shapes onscreen in
> AMIGA mode in a way my Amiga will love?

First of all: instead of your own display creation, open a Screen, using
#Screen# or #ScreenTags# command. Make the bitmaps as you did in Blitz mo=
de,
same with shapes. Also #Blit# and #BBlit# everything. But use #ShowBitMap=
#
instead
of #DisplayBitMap#. That should be it. There are some changes in keyboard=

reading, if you have it and you'll have to open a borderless window, if y=
ou
use Edit or Edit$.

Hope, this was of some help.

Regards

Damir

