    10 Jul 98 12:41:50 +0100
    10 Jul 98 12:41:37 +0100
From: "Dermot Smyth" <D.P.Smyth@sheffield.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: Collision detectioin
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 1998 12:41:40 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi,

>is it possible to detect collisions between two shapes...

ShapesHit(Shape#,x,y,Shape#,x,y)
(page 162 of manual)

>or between a shape and the background?

I don`t know about this, do you mean background as in the bitmap or
background as in a map feature (like a rock or tree)?

I do my collision using palette colours because ShapesHit is too blocky and
inaccurate (it doesn`t account for the colour 0 empty spaces in your shape,
so you get collisions occuring in "thin air").

>>>>ALEX<<<< Smyth




