@NODE "Mail.301" "Re: CMAP"
From: "Paul West" <paul@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Date: 27 Jul 98 13:33:26 +0000
Subject: Re: CMAP

> >  They
> > don't even explain what a "CMAP" file is!
> 
> A CMAP is really a "chunk" contained in any .iff picture file, which stores
> the colour info.

> Paint programs actually save palettes as an iff "picture", size 0x0, complete
> with a standard .iff header.

Technically speaking, there is no such thing as an iff picture or an
iff colourmap. IFF is the Interchangeable File Format which is able to
store a selection of data formats including sounds, pictures, and
animations. Pictures are referred to as ILBM, an InterLeaved BitMap.

I know what you mean though, I have a drawer on my hd for `iff
pictures'. ;)

--
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk




@ENDNODE
