------=_NextPart_000_00C9_01BDA297.644D7080
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hope nobody minds, but here is the EXCELLENT EML CIA tracker replay library
be Paul Reece. It is the best thing ever, and, unlike the XBones lib, works
on all processors. The only downside is the inability to "cludge" modules,
but hey!

Nick Chapman / Skillo Software Interactive
scillo@mailexcite.com
http://www.bomb.demon.co.uk

-----Original Message-----
From: Frank Otto <Robocop@dame.de>
Date: 24 June 1998 18:20
Subject: CIATrackerLib


>Hi,
>
>I've been using the CIATrackerLib for some time now and was satisfied with
>it (compared to the Blitz commands for module playing it's perfect) but
right
>now it does not work! And I don't know why!
>
>a=StartTracker(0) returns 'true' but there's no sound! The Blitz commands
>still work but are not useable for 'good' module playing.
>
>I've also tried to use the "XbonesCIAlibrary" but this one only works in
Blitz
>mode. So it's not useable too.
>
>Anyone knowing why this happens? Why is there no sound with the
CIATrackerLibrary?
>
>Maybe you can recommend another method or another good library than the
CIATrackerLib?
>
>
>
>thanks
>--
>Frank
