@NODE "Mail.310" "Re: Chunky 2 Planar"
From: "Paul West" <paul@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Date: 24 Jul 98 00:29:42 +0000
Subject: Re: Chunky 2 Planar

Andreas,

> Before I`ll try to adapt c2p src`s to Blitz I`ve some questions....
> 
> 1) Is it possible with AGA c2p to smoothscroll a 200x180x8 shape on a
> 320x256x8
>      bitmap?

Depends entirely on your cpu. I see you have an 040, so the answer is
yes. But not at 50fps. 25fps definately. In fact, with 040, you should
be able to c2p 320x256 at about 38fps and then the time remaining can
be used for blitting and so on. It works out you could probably
smoothly scroll a full screen any still maintain 25fps, if not more.
 
> 2) Are there any demo c2p src`s for blitz to get some impression of it? 

I posted one just recently. It's for 040 or 060's only and uses write
caches for boosting speed. For 320x256 it's 10 frames per second
faster than any other one I could find. If you cannot find it in your
storage of past messages let me know.

You have 040. I can only assume that's 25Mhz but it could be 33 or 40.

You must bear in mind that 50fps using chunky is totally out of the
question at 320x256 unless you have an 060, although 320x200 c2p runs
at 50fps on 040/25. This does not however take into account time
needed for actually blitting some stuff, but if you do have 040/25 and
you use a screen of less height (even 320x240 or 320x220) you will
gain some considerable blit-time.

If you were using 320x200 at 50fps you could have your game run at
25fps and blit probably getting on for 3-4 fullscreens if you wanted.

--
Paul.

