@NODE "Mail.321" "Re: Can you solve this(Math problems)??"
Date: Wed, 29 Jul 1998 09:56:19 -0500
From: Bohdan Lechnowsky <bohdan_lechnowsky@csgsystems.com>
Subject: Re: Can you solve this(Math problems)??

Try this:

;Figure out what the distance is between the x and y beginning and
ending
; coordinates
dx=x2-x1
dy=y2-y1

;Figure out which distance is greater (x or y) and assign it to a
variable
if dx>dy then biggest=dx
else biggest=dy

;Make an array just big enough to hold the points for the line
dim linearrayx.f(biggest)
dim linearrayy.f(biggest)

;Figure out what the increment is for each point in the x and y
directions
incx.f=dx/biggest
incy.f=dy/biggest

;Initialize the array with the starting point
linearrayx(0)=x1
linearrayy(0)=y1

;This loop will increment through the largest distance and assign the
points
; to the array
for i=1 to biggest
   linearrayx(i)=linearrayx(i-1)+incx
   linearrayy(i)=linearrayy(i-1)+incy
   ;You could also put your plot command right here
next

Voila!  That should do it.  Piece of cake.

-Bo
 Global Posse Software

P.S.  I just used a very similar routine to this for a 3D game I wrote
on my Psion Series 5.  This is pseudocode, but I imagine it should work
as typed.

