Dear Jon, what you need is that thing which I love so much,
bresenham's line routine. It's very cool the way it works, entirely
with integer maths.

I saw that bahdan lechnowsky sent you a response about this but it
uses floating point and that is quite slow (but straightforward).

I once wrote a very long and useful text about bresenhams integer
scaling. It is certainly what you need , as it does a most elegant
line-draw and you can also use it for integer scaling in other ways
(texturemapping, zooming, etc). I will probably have to get into this
myself in the very near future.

I will write it for you in a seperate message so that it is clearer to
others and they can then find some use of it also.

-- 
Paul.

