@NODE "Mail.344" "BUMs etc."
From: "Tri" <scillo@geocities.com>
Subject: BUMs etc.
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 1998 17:13:44 +0100
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_00BF_01BDAE81.97923E80"

This is a multi-part message in MIME format.

------=_NextPart_000_00BF_01BDAE81.97923E80
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi all,

Okay, let's sort this out once and for all...

The Blitz User Magazine series got up to issue 10. BUMs 9 and 10 were =
not distributed to registered users at all. They are only available from =
Guildhall Leisure in the UK and cost =A310 for a nifty little pack =
containing both the disks and the info. Previous BUMs were given to =
registered users, and BUMs 5-8 were given away by CU-Amiga on their =
April 1996 CD. Since they are 1MB each, nobody is going to be very =
amused if I post them here! I can tell you now that none of the BUMs =
have much that is of any use these days apart from certain handy =
snippets of source code. The libraries are in common circulation, and =
Blitz 2.1 comes with all of the libraries contained in BUMs 1-8 anyway. =
The source code can be useful if it covers something you need. In the =
case of everybody's current object of desire, the texture mapping demo =
on BUM 10 is rubbish. It takes a 4-colour fireball of 32x32 pixels, and =
spends about 3 seconds texture mapping it onto a planar screen. Amazing =
a few years ago, but tosh now. What we really want is for someone to =
write a speedy texture-mapping demo using current C2P techniques. Any =
takers?

Oh, and let's not cane Acid too much. If it weren't for them, Blitz =
wouldn't exist at all. Yes, Blitz has loads of flaws, and the manual is =
rubbish. But Blitz was evolving and becoming better all the time, and =
would have continued to do so. It was the collapse in the commercial =
Amiga market which made them pull out. Curse Commodore & ESCOM. Perhaps =
GW2K can revive the Amiga scene...please let it be true...

As for the manual, see my next email!

Nick Chapman / Skillo Software Interactive
scillo@mailexcite.com
http://www.bomb.demon.co.uk

------=_NextPart_000_00BF_01BDAE81.97923E80
