Hi,

Another pearl from the best manual ever....

Here is the info on the Screenpens command from the manual:

Screenpens active text, inactive text, hilight,shadow, active fill, gadget
fill
(thats 6 parameters)

Cool eh? Now here's the info from the Help within Blitz:

Screenpens text, shine, shadow, fill, filltext, background, highlight
(thats 7 parameters folks)

Excellent, now, both docs say that the Screenpen command changes the
10 default pens. Yes 10. So wheres the other 3/4???!!!!!

Thanks Blitz manual, I love you ;))))))

I'm in the middle of frustration right now, I'll be back on when I've
finally
