@NODE "Mail.355" "Re: Break! (from another)"
	(envelope-from rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    30 Jul 98 09:31:25 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Thu, 30 Jul 1998 09:31:18 +0100
Subject: Re: Break! (from another)

On 29 Jul 98, at 10:30, Mathias PARNAUDEAU gave this nugget of information:


<color><param>7F00,0000,0000</param>> But how can I do if I want to wait for the mouse clicked ?

> Is there a corresponding event for this ?


</color> If you have a window open then you can specify the 
#IDCMP_MOUSEBUTTONS flag when you open it - this will give 
you an event when a mouse button is pressed. If you don't have a 
window open, then you will need to create a message port, add the 
#IDCMP_MOUSEBUTTONS flag to it then do an AddWaitEvent for 
that message port.


> Where are the documentation about kinds of events (if exists ;-) ?


 Probably in the RKRMs (which I don't have), various C manuals on 
Aminet. You can get a lot of information by looking at the 
autodocs. Just check out some of the names of the commands in 
the library and if any catch your eye, then read it. Also looking at C 
source code is very helpful for stuff that's anywhere near the OS.



<nofill>
.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.
|rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk|



