    28 Jul 98 16:08:48 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Tue, 28 Jul 1998 16:08:40 +0100
Subject: Re: Break!

Following on from pressing the send button by mistake (doh)...

if you have the AddWaitEvent command then you can do (you'll 
need amigalibs.res resident for this)

AddWaitEvent #SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C

and then it will be detected, when you have and Event or WaitEvent 
in your code, and someone has pressed Ctrl-C.

If this doesn't work then its because I don't have wherever the 
AddWaitEvent command comes from, but I could send some 
source to do it with OS functions.


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.
|rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk|



