    1 Jul 98 22:48:12 +0100
    1 Jul 98 22:47:52 +0100
From: "Dermot Smyth" <D.P.Smyth@sheffield.ac.uk>
Subject: Bloomin` cpu blitting
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 1998 22:47:54 +0100
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_001B_01BDA542.48A8F9A0"

This is a multi-part message in MIME format.

------=_NextPart_000_001B_01BDA542.48A8F9A0
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi,

I`m still having problems putting in Dave Newton`s cpu blitting commands =
into my program.
I`m doing the SUPERBITMAP-FASTBUFFER-CHIP method.
The problem is that when I copy the FASTBUFFER into CHIP all I get is a =
starfield type hash :/
I tested copying from the SUPERBITMAP into CHIP and the same thing =
happened, so er....
Do the bitmaps have to be the same width?
Has anyone experienced this?
Does anyone have a little example prog of the =
SUPERBITMAP-FASTBUFFER-CHIP method using Dave`s routines that they could =
send?
For some reason it worked on my previous version (FAST BITMAP - CHIP) =
but not the superbitmap method. I`ve checked through everything as well, =
so I`m stumped.

>>>ALEX<<< Smyth

------=_NextPart_000_001B_01BDA542.48A8F9A0
	charset="iso-8859-1"

