@NODE "Mail.368" "Blitz OS Tutorials"
Newsgroups: BLITZ-LIST
X-FTN-To: Cox, Michael D
Date: 23 Jul 98 01:45:35 GMT
X-GateSoftware: AmiGate 1.4b (26.6.95)
X-Plug: Xenolink, No. 1 BBS Software for the Amiga!
From: bml@darkside.demon.co.uk (Simon Archer)
Subject: Blitz OS Tutorials

On 17 Jul 98 Cox, Michael D wrote about 'Blitz OS Tutorials'.

 CMD> I have not tried the program on AmiNet that will convert those .gui
 CMD> files for use with BB2 but does it support the newest GTB (v3) or just
 CMD> v2.0c (or something like that)?

As the creator of one of these converters, I'd just like to add that the use
of BlitzGUIGen is more than just a gui creator. It includes some source
components that are of great tutorial value. The source is well commented
and laid out. This makes the source extremely easy to understand and follow.

Try it and see how you get on. You may be surprised.

Simon Archer





@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.369" "Re: Blitz Manual"
	(envelope-from rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    27 Jul 98 09:23:15 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Mon, 27 Jul 1998 09:23:00 +0100
Subject: Re: Blitz Manual

On 26 Jul 98, at 16:18, Alex Smyth gave this nugget of information:

> Hi,
> 
> Another ridiculous thing from the manual....

 At least it's consistent...
 
> OK, so I looked in the manual to see what was
> wrong and it said that it saves an IFF "CMAP"
> palette.
> 
> My thoughts were...
> OK..."CMAP" what!? :/
>
> Why the hell shouldn't it save a normal
> palette file that PP could load in! I mean
> if it loads in a normal palette why doesn't
> it save one!? It makes no sense.  They
> don't even explain what a "CMAP" file is!

 That is a normal palette type (use a hex editor to look at a saved 
bitmap - it will have CMAP in it somewhere). CMAP stands for 
ColourMAP, but that's all I know I'm afraid.


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.
|rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk|



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.370" "Blitz Manual"
    26 Jul 98 16:19:05 +0100
    26 Jul 98 16:18:50 +0100
From: "Dermot Smyth" <D.P.Smyth@sheffield.ac.uk>
Subject: Blitz Manual
Date: Sun, 26 Jul 1998 16:18:48 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Hi,

Another ridiculous thing from the manual....

I needed to save a palette and seeing as there 
was a LoadPalette command I presumed that
the SavePalette command would be the same
(except opposite, natch).  So I went ahead
and saved the palette.  Then I tried to load the
palette into Personal Paint but guess what...it
wouldn't load!  It said that it was a unrecognised
format.

OK, so I looked in the manual to see what was
wrong and it said that it saves an IFF "CMAP"
palette.

My thoughts were...
OK..."CMAP" what!? :/

Why the hell shouldn't it save a normal
palette file that PP could load in! I mean
if it loads in a normal palette why doesn't
it save one!? It makes no sense.  They
don't even explain what a "CMAP" file is!

I got around it though by saving a bitmap
instead, with the palette attached and then
PP could load it but I don't like doing it 
because it should save a normal palette!

Does anyone know a way to save a normal
palette, a different library or something?

Anyway, that person who was going to 
write a new manual....PLEASE WRITE IT!

We need deliverance! :)

:)

>>>ALEX<<< Smyth




@ENDNODE
