  It's not legit.  The people who wrote the Blitz Support Suite have
stated publically that Guildhall neither asked them permission to
include it nor payed them for it.  They could sue, and maybe they are
or will if they figure it's worth it.  I believe I would sue just on
principle, especially since it seems Guildhall have no intention of
setting things right nor even apologizing.  Piracy by a large
company who apparently believes they can get away with it.  Stinks, eh?
Are they related to microsoft?  Sounds like their style.


Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)





