@NODE "Mail.386" "Re: Black Screen"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Jul 1998 06:19:39 -0500
Subject: Re: Black Screen

Hi Andreas

On 29-Jul-98, Andreas Etzrodt wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> how do I open a totally black screen (with the "normal" 
> Blitz-Screen-command)? At the moment I open the screen
> and fade the palette to black. But when I do it this
> way the screen flashes shortly in his original colors
> and then disappears (fades). Is it possible to open a
> screen which is black from the beginning?

Try this, it might help:

InitPalette 0,(number of colours)  ;makes an all black palette
(open your screen here)
Use Palette 0                      ;show the black palette

If this flashes too, you can make the screen in back of the display, then pop
it in front when it is ready.  You'll need to use ScreenTags command for this.



                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/





@ENDNODE
