@NODE "Mail.388" "BBlit/Unbuffer replacement?"
>X-Dummy: YES
X-ZC-VIA: 19980708000000S+2@dame.de
Subject: BBlit/Unbuffer replacement?
From: Robocop@dame.de (Frank Otto)
Date: Wed,  8 Jul 1998 15:25:54 +0200
X-Gateway: ZCONNECT dame.de [UUWORLD RFC/ZC V2.2 SER#A4583577]

Hello,

who knows the source behind 'BBlit' and 'Unbuffer'? We all know that both
commands are buggy: When unbuffering a shape, an area of X=32 pixels
replaces the BBlitted shape but my shapes are only X=16 Pixels so other
shapes in that area are destroyed !

Can someone help me on this?

I already thought about just blitting the shapes (not BBlitting them)
but how can I store the background ? Using 'GetAShape' is not a good idea.

If I only knew how this Buffered Blitting works...



And A SECOND question (maybe a solution to my first question):

How does double buffering work without using bblit /unbuffer?

With those commands it should look like this:

With                     Without

---------------
repeat

vwait

..
..
..

display bitmap db

db=1-db
use bitmap db
unbuffer 1-db            Blit (Background shapes)   *
bblit db,shape,x,y       Blit (player for example)

forever

---------------------------------------------

* I know which shapes to use here

Is this correct? With BBlit/Unbuffer it works fine here but without
it looks ugly (the player shapes are not removed properly. It looks like
I had no double buffered display. But I have!)

Anything I have forgotten in the source?



I hope You can help me!


Thanks!

--
Frank





