Date: 3 Aug 98 13:03:06 +0000
Subject: Re: BBlit Clipping

> Can someone give me a definite answer as to BBlit Clipping please.
> I've heard some people say they thought you could do it but no-one
> seems to know commands for it. The manual certainly doesn't have any
> (although there is one for normal Blit).
> 
> It seems a bit unwise to have no clipping routines as currently all my
> bitmaps have to have an extra 160 pixels on EACH side of them (my
> shapes are quite big). This uses up a ridiculous extra amount of chip
> memory which could be saved by a simple clipping routine.
> 
> All I need is either the name of a command I've missed or maybe an
> extension or even a routine to do it myself (without using an extra
> bitmap - memory).
> 
> Thanks,
> -Murray
> 
> --
> 
>  Alastair  \\|//   malcolm.murray@virgin.net
