@NODE "Mail.392" "Bad Trip!"
From: Rui de Carvalho <grim@esoterica.pt>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 1998 12:18:59 +0100
Subject: Bad Trip!

Hello ppl,

Well it seems Acid has gone bad, i registered myself in March 1997, i nev=
er
received anything Acid, not even a small card saying thanks, nada, ziltch=
,
zero. If i ever contacted them, they would even be able to identify me (n=
o
registration number!). Then in January 98 i bougth Ultimate Blitz CD, thi=
s
time there wasn't a even a registration card in it. If it wasn't for the
dedication of the people on this list and those who work in Blitz, i'm su=
re it
would have ended has many other programing languages.

About BUMs copyright, i've never seen it written on any of the disks. BUI=
 on
the other hand is copyrighted.
I'm going to try to contact the author of BUM and Acid to ask for their
permission to include all of the BUMs in my site.

But for some strange reason i don't think i'll be able to reach them...
[ACID is probably in Hawai, enjoying a large vacation on our expence :)]


This comes to prove one point, some drugs aren't worth it! =



Best Regards
