@NODE "Mail.402" "Re: AppIcon ;)"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@hol.fr>
Date: Thu, 30 Jul 1998 19:35:25 +0100
Subject: Re: AppIcon ;)

    Hi OPi^Plastic!, =


> Yello,
> =

> Another creazy problem ;)
> =

> Look at this part of code
> =

> If AddAppIcon(0,"My App Icon!","ram:app")
>   DeleteFile_ ("ram:app.info") ;it's displayed allready
>   ; =

>   ;You prog or anything Ya like ;)
>   ;
> else
>   putstr_ ("Total fu*** up!")
>   end
> =

> Looks OK? And even works! Then why I writin' this letter?
> Cause under icon (app of coure) i don't get "My App Icon!" only
> "ram:app.info"...Strange ehh? =

> But if I remove DeleteFile ("ram:app.info") I get correctly label under=

> icon....Hmmmm.....I try to add Delay_20....so now I got
> <...>
> Delay_20
> DeleteFile ("ram:app.info")

    Hey, it's normal. The Amiga is being creating your AppIcon and do you=
 know
what ? You want to kill it ! The Amiga has a 'lock' objects system which
prevent to delete object which are always in use. It's very useful. In yo=
ur
case, insert a little delay and let's go. A loop which check the deletefi=
le_()
result is another solution (better ?).

    bye,

        Fred.

