@NODE "Mail.403" "Re: AppIcon ;)"
 Thu, 30 Jul 1998 11:51:49 -0400
From: "Garfield Benjamin" <gbenjam@sosbbs.com>
Subject: Re: AppIcon ;)
Date: Thu, 30 Jul 1998 12:13:38 -0400

> Look at this part of code
>   If AddAppIcon(0,"My App Icon!","ram:app")
>      DeleteFile_ ("ram:app.info") ;it's displayed allready
>      ;You prog or anything Ya like ;)
>   Else
>      putstr_ ("Total fu*** up!")
>   End If
> i don't get "My App Icon!" only "ram:app.info"...Strange ehh? 
> I try to add Delay_20....so now I got 
>   Delay_20
>   DeleteFile ("ram:app.info")
> And It WORKS! Now could anybody explain me WHY I NEED TO ADD
> DELAY BEFORE ERASING ICON FILE???!?

   Don't know exactly why but I have always said that in my programming
   experience (particularly on the Amiga) bugs seem to occur more often
   from processing certain things too quickly than any other reason.  About
   80% of all the bugs I've encountered have been fixed by inserting a tiny
   delay just as you have found...  I'm really going out on a limb but I
   think it might be possible that due to the Amiga's multitasking OS
   certain tasks (such as your use of DeleteFile) are completed before
   others which actually should be completed first based on their
   positioning in the code.  Again, that's really just a shot in the
   dark... all I know is that for 17 years now I've noticed that computers
   can't handle certain operations being performed too close/too quick
   and the Amiga seems to suffer from this more than any other machine
   I've programmed on. 


                Garfield Benjamin    e-mail:gbenjam@sosbbs.com
                     Website( http://www.sosbbs.com/~gbenjam )



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail.404" "AppIcon ;)"
