From: Andreas =?iso-8859-1?Q?H=E5kansson?= <andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com>
Date: Fri, 03 Jul 1998 00:29:24 +0100
Subject: Accessing the serial device, using OS-Calls


 Hiya!

Does anyone know how you use the serial device from blitz, by
using the OS calls? I know you use the OpenDevice_ command to
open it, and I know you have to setup an ioRequester by using
DEFTYPE.ioRequest <variabel>. Now the thing is, how do I set
up the <variabel> so that it can be used to send and receive
data? I know there is a io_Message and a io_Command variabel
in the .ioRequest structure, but I dont know how to setup
them properbly to be used with a send routine as well as with
an receive routine. So if anyone with C knowlage could give
me an example on how to do this, then PLEASE DO!! I really
need it, and the Blitz serial commands is really messed up.
I can get them to work with the Serial.device, but when I
try to use the duart.device from blitz it wont work. I know
I'm doing the right thing (I just changed the device$ name,
to the right one). I know that my duart.device works, since
I've managed to use it from AMOS (please forgive me, hehe).

So if anyone out there posses the knowlage on how to use the
serial.device from blitz, using OS calls, or if someone has
some example source on how to do this, then please share
your knowlage with me.

Thanks in advance,

  Andreas

