@NODE "Mail.416" "Re: Accessing Libraries part 3"
	(envelope-from rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    14 Jul 98 09:31:35 GMT+1
From: "David McMinn" <rsdm@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 1998 09:31:21 +0100
Subject: Re: Accessing Libraries part 3

On 13 Jul 98, at 7:31, Cox, Michael D tippy-tappy-typed:

> I am still having the same problem (the command name changes) but I have a
> question.  On my Ultimate BB2 CD there is not a BASIC or SYSTEM directory
> under BlitzLibs.  On my old v1.7 floppy disk there is and in the LibDev
> documentation they mention these directories.  Should these directories
> exist?  Should I just copy them over from v1.7 or are there newer ones or
> what?  To say the least, this is getting frustrating so any help would be
> appreciated.

 No, these drawers were replaced by the acidlibs file. As for library numbers, I think the 
first half (0 - 127) are used in the "official" libraries that are released and 128 - 255 are used 
for while developing libraries, so try using some from there. I've got 4 other libraries that are 
at 217-200.

Note to everyone:
 Remember, if you use any extra libraries and send the tokenised source to the list, 
chances are that some other people will have different libs at those numbers, and won't be 
able to make sense of your source.


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.



