@NODE "Mail.418" "Re: Accessing Libraries part 2"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 1998 11:55:19 +0000
Subject: Re: Accessing Libraries part 2
Annouce: Amiga - Back for the Future

I watched as Cox, Michael D hammered "Accessing Libraries part 2" out
on their keyboard...
> Okay, I looked in the LibDev directory and it told me to use the
> Fdconvert tool.  I did this and it made the library for me. I
recreated
> deflibs (ran the Makedeflibs program) and restarted BB2.  Now, when
I
> type in a function from that library, it changes the name to
something
> else.  For instance, a function is date_Compare2Dates_ and it gets
> changed to SysJsr.  What is causing this?

You've got a library conflict, 2 libs are sharing the same number so
Blitz doesn't know which to use.

> Also, how does one know what library numbers are being used? I guess
I
> can use ViewLibs but it does not exactly sort them in any way.

Look on Aminet for "BlitzLibMan" or something like that, it'll find
unused lib numbers and compile deflibs for you, among other things.

See ya!

/Rick/
-- 
